an>Hans Peter Isler, «L’agora ellenistica di Iaitas», in \u003Ci>Agora greca e agorai di Sicilia\u003C/i>, a c. di Carmine Ampolo (Pisa: Edizioni della Normale, 2012), 229–37\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/GU7UQJGD",{"editor":185,"principal":188,"contributors":189,"change":203},{"_":186,"ref":187},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":186,"ref":187},[190,193,197,201],{"_":186,"xml:id":191,"ref":192},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":194,"xml:id":195,"ref":196},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":198,"xml:id":199,"ref":200},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"xml:id":202},"MMohr",{"_":204,"when":205,"who":187},"Jonathan Prag created file from template based upon information from Martin Mohr and publications","2021-04-30",{"n":108,"url":109,"height":110,"width":111,"desc":112,"surfaceType":113},[],[209,210,211],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Isler, 1995, Monte Iato: la venticinquesima campagna di scavo","Isler, 1996, Grabungen auf dem Monte Iato 1995",[213,214,215],"F2GG87EQ","5HTNILI3","4D2UL73J",[217,218,219,22,27,31,220,221,222,223,224,225,226,135],"isic030048","fragment of a greek inscription on bronze",{"_":5},"ietas","monte iato","sicilia","sicily","san cipirello","depot of the zurich ietas excavation","ancient greek",[],{"title":229,"body":230,"divs":231,"editions":256,"images":266,"handnote":272},"ISic030048. Fragment of a Greek inscription on bronze","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΘΙΑΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΟΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΘΙΑΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΟΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic030048_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo courtesy Zurich Ietas excavations\" src=\"ISic030048_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic030048.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo courtesy Zurich Ietas excavations\" src=\"ISic030048-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Isler: ΡΣΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The fragment is one of three metal fragments reported by Isler from the Ietas excavations (the other two, unpublished, are Latin fragments: \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic030049\" target=\"_blank\">ISic030049\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic030050\" target=\"_blank\">ISic030050\u003C/a>). Isler draws comparison with the Entella tablets, and it is a reasonable assumption that this is the remains of a public text, possibly originally on display in the area of the agora or associated public buildings. The letter forms are compatible with a third-century BCE date, but precision is impossible. Isler reads the first letter of line 3 as Ρ, but omicron seems much more likely, firstly because of the unlikely sequence ΡΣ and secondly by comparison with the rho in line 1 and the theta in line 2, and the absence of any trace of a straight vertical on the left side of the letter.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 46.1257 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Isler 1995 20 with fig. 9 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002488\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002488\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Isler 1996 54 with taf. 10.5 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002489\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002489\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Isler 2012 234 with n.41 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001361\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001361\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Deeply engraved letters of slightly varying height (omicron/theta small and midline, iota extended beyond other letters). Letters have pronounced circular terminations to many strokes (punched). Alpha has straight bar; epsilon has short middle stroke; theta is small and midline with central point; iota is tall; pi has verticals of equal length; rho appears open; sigma has diverging upper and lower strokes.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence \u003C/div>",[232,235,238,241,244,247,250,253],{"id":233,"html":234},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΘΙΑΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΟΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΘΙΑΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΟΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":236,"html":237},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic030048_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo courtesy Zurich Ietas excavations\" src=\"ISic030048_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic030048.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo courtesy Zurich Ietas excavations\" src=\"ISic030048-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":239,"html":240},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Isler: ΡΣΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":242,"html":243},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":245,"html":246},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The fragment is one of three metal fragments reported by Isler from the Ietas excavations (the other two, unpublished, are Latin fragments: \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic030049\" target=\"_blank\">ISic030049\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic030050\" target=\"_blank\">ISic030050\u003C/a>). Isler draws comparison with the Entella tablets, and it is a reasonable assumption that this is the remains of a public text, possibly originally on display in the area of the agora or associated public buildings. The letter forms are compatible with a third-century BCE date, but precision is impossible. Isler reads the first letter of line 3 as Ρ, but omicron seems much more likely, firstly because of the unlikely sequence ΡΣ and secondly by comparison with the rho in line 1 and the theta in line 2, and the absence of any trace of a straight vertical on the left side of the letter.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":248,"html":249},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 46.1257 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Isler 1995 20 with fig. 9 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002488\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002488\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Isler 1996 54 with taf. 10.5 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002489\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002489\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Isler 2012 234 with n.41 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001361\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001361\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":251,"html":252},"handnote","\u003Cp>Deeply engraved letters of slightly varying height (omicron/theta small and midline, iota extended beyond other letters). Letters have pronounced circular terminations to many strokes (punched). Alpha has straight bar; epsilon has short middle stroke; theta is small and midline with central point; iota is tall; pi has verticals of equal length; rho appears open; sigma has diverging upper and lower strokes.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":254,"html":255},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence ",[257,259,262,263],{"html":258},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":260,"lang":135,"html":261},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΠΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] 